Magnesium bromide is one of the most abundant compounds found in sea water. Which formula correctly represents magnesium bromide? Choose the correct answer from the following options:
(A) MgBr
(B) MgBr_{2}
(C) Mg_{2}Br
(D) Mg_{3}Br_{2}

A student placed a living green plant in an airtight, transparent container filled with air from the room. The container was exposed to sunlight for one week. At the end of the week the student was to determine which gases had increased in concentration. Assuming enough water and carbon dioxide were available for the proper growth of the plant, which gas would you expect to be present in increased concentration? Choose the correct answer from the following options:
(A) C
(B) NO_{2}
(C) O_{2}
(D) CO

Significant destruction of a forest habitat will increase which gas in the atmosphere? Choose the correct answer from the following options:
(A) CO_{2}
(B) NO_{2}
(C) O_{2}
(D) N_{2}

An aluminum ion has a charge of +3, and an oxide ion has a charge of -2. Which would be the product of a reaction between these two elements? Choose the correct answer from the following options:
(A) Al_{2}O
(B) Al_{2}O_{3}
(C) 2AlO_{3}
(D) Al_{3}O_{2}

If HCl is added to Zn, what would be an expected product? Choose the correct answer from the following options:
(A) Cl_{2}
(B) HZn
(C) ZnCl
(D) ZnCl_{2}

Which of the following is a correctly written chemical equation that demonstrates the conservation of mass? Choose the correct answer from the following options:
(A) Mg + HCl -> H_{2} + MgCl_{2}
(B) H_{2}O + CO_{2} -> H_{2}CO_{3}
(C) KClO_{3} -> KCl + O_{2}
(D) H_{2} + O_{2} -> H_{2}O
